        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-26T18:00:13.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"166734\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Paired amazing with Christmas lunch of seared jumbo sea scallops, beurre blanc and shaved black truffles. Really brought out the tropical spices like nutmeg and cinnamon.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3195685&amp;iNote=8852844\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2017 Olivier Leflaive B\u00e2tard-Montrachet</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, B\u00e2tard-Montrachet Grand Cru (12/25/2020)</em><br>\nDiam 10. Decanted. Opened up after 30-40 minutes to reveal an elegant and sophisticated nose of white flowers, peach pit, wet stone. Palate is rich and weighty, coating the tongue with pear, yellow peach, underripe pineapple and a touch of lime zest and a hint of warm tropical spices. Loaded with acidity, the finish goes on and on. Extremely solid and should develop nicely for many years. Sad that I had Coravin\u2019d this bottle in Feb and wasn\u2019t impressed and didn\u2019t buy more. <em><strong>(95 pts.)</strong></em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Was this the Maison or \u201cR\u00e9colte du Domaine\u201d bottling?</p>",
