        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-26T21:32:13.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"166734\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"166734\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Was this the Maison or \u201cR\u00e9colte du Domaine\u201d bottling?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I assume Maison as the bottle doesn\u2019t say anything in particular.</p>\n<p>I scanned the barcode on the bottle and it took me here: <a href=\"https://m.olivier-leflaive.com/8U3EWE\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://m.olivier-leflaive.com/8U3EWE</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, that\u2019s Maison then! I think the Maison wines are good, but the r\u00e9colte du domaine cuv\u00e9es are really first rate and deserve a lot more acclaim and attention than they have received, so if you ever see any of those, try them!</p>",
